    {
      "title": "Advanced idioms, proverbs and figures of speech",
      "html": "<p>Senior candidates must recognise <b>advanced idioms</b> — fixed expressions whose meaning is not literal.</p>\n  <ul>\n    <li><i>a wolf in sheep's clothing</i> — a dangerous person pretending to be harmless.</li>\n    <li><i>bite the bullet</i> — accept an unpleasant duty bravely.</li>\n    <li><i>call it a day</i> — stop working.</li>\n    <li><i>cut corners</i> — do something in the easiest but poorest way.</li>\n    <li><i>the ball is in your court</i> — it is your turn to decide.</li>\n    <li><i>throw in the towel</i> — give up.</li>\n    <li><i>hit the nail on the head</i> — describe something exactly right.</li>\n    <li><i>a storm in a teacup</i> — a big fuss about a small matter.</li>\n  </ul>\n  <p><b>Proverbs</b> compress wisdom: <i>A stitch in time saves nine; too many cooks spoil the broth; every cloud has a silver lining; when the going gets tough, the tough get going.</i></p>",
      "examples": [
        {
          "q": "Explain <i>throw in the towel</i>.",
          "a": "To give up (from boxing, where the trainer throws in a towel to signal surrender)."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Registers — Aviation, Maritime, Commerce, Banking, Administration",
      "html": "<p><b>Aviation</b>: cockpit, cabin crew, altitude, turbulence, runway, taxiing, boarding pass, aviation fuel, air-traffic control, hangar, jet lag, itinerary, callsign.</p>\n  <p><b>Maritime</b>: vessel, cargo, port, harbour, quay, buoy, anchor, stevedore, freight, bill of lading, keel, deck, mast, tanker.</p>\n  <p><b>Commerce</b>: retailer, wholesaler, invoice, quotation, discount, dispatch, warehouse, consignment, gross, net, turnover, credit facility.</p>\n  <p><b>Banking</b>: deposit, withdrawal, ledger, overdraft, credit balance, interest rate, mortgage, cheque, standing order, remittance, teller.</p>\n  <p><b>Administration</b>: memorandum, agenda, minutes, quorum, resolution, ex-officio, delegation, dossier, protocol, secretariat.</p>",
      "examples": [
        {
          "q": "Which register is <i>bill of lading</i>?",
          "a": "Maritime (shipping) — the document listing goods being shipped."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Advanced word study",
      "html": "<p>Beyond memorising lists, examine words by their <b>parts</b>:</p>\n  <ul>\n    <li><b>Prefix</b> — added at the front (<i>un-, dis-, mis-, over-, anti-, pre-</i>): <i>uneducated, mislead, overrule, anti-social.</i></li>\n    <li><b>Root</b> — the core meaning (<i>bene</i> = good; <i>ject</i> = throw; <i>graph</i> = write).</li>\n    <li><b>Suffix</b> — added at the end (<i>-ness, -ity, -ment, -tion, -able</i>): <i>happiness, ability, movement, decision, readable.</i></li>\n  </ul>\n  <p>Use word roots to guess meaning: <i>benefactor</i> — someone who <b>does good</b> (bene + factor).</p>",
      "examples": [
        {
          "q": "Break down <i>unhappiness</i>: prefix / root / suffix.",
          "a": "un- (prefix, not) + happy (root) + -ness (suffix, state). Meaning: state of not being happy."
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
